author: Aaron Wilson
title: Texans' Duane Brown presents Community Quarterback award - Houston Chronicle
text:
Texans' Duane Brown presents Community Quarterback award 1 / 1 Back to Gallery 
Veteran offensive tackle Duane Brown presented David Baldwin with the Texans' Community Quarterback award grand prize Tuesday. 
Baldwin was recognized for his work at a reception as a board member and longtime community partner at The Center, which assists individuals with disabilities. 
"It means a lot," Brown said. "It's a great company, great organization. The work they do in the community is amazing. It's emphasizing volunteering. We recognize a special person who's done the most." 
A former first-round draft pick and a three-time Pro Bowl selection, Brown is one of the Texans' most community-oriented players. 
"It's been amazing," Brown said. "I've been here nine years. Being in the community has always been a big part of my progression and evolution as a player and person in this community. They embrace the team very well, the city does. It's only right that we give back."
